# Presentations — slide discipline

Read [`presentations/SLIDE-RULES.md`](../../presentations/SLIDE-RULES.md) before editing or adding slides.

## One-slide budget

Each `##` slide: **one** primary block (≤4 bullets, or ≤3-row table, or ≤5-line code) + **≤2** supporting lines. No stacking table + bullets + blockquote + citations.

## Overflow

Split slides (`continued`, `— diagram`). Move qualifications and long paths to HTML speaker notes. Never delete concepts to fit.

## Appendix

Reading-map slides: **2 entries** each (path + one-line why).

## After edits

Remind author to Marp-preview and PDF-export; flag slides that likely exceed budget before claiming done.
